VALUES
(44, 13, 14, 44, 13, 5, 5, NULL, 'Preaching in Synagogues', 'Both passages emphasize the act of preaching in synagogues, highlighting the importance of these locations for the early Christian mission. The mention of synagogues in both contexts connects their ministry efforts.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 14, 44, 14, 19, 19, 'Antioch in Pisidia', 'Persecution of Paul', 'Both passages emphasize the hostility Paul faced in Antioch. The stoning in Acts 14:19 follows his arrival in Antioch in Acts 13:14, illustrating the escalating opposition he encountered.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 14, 44, 17, 2, 2, 'sabbath day', 'Sabbath Day Worship', 'Both passages emphasize the practice of gathering on the sabbath day for teaching and discussion. This connection highlights Paul''s consistent approach in engaging with the scriptures during these gatherings.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 14, 44, 18, 4, 4, 'on the sabbath day', 'Sabbath Synagogue Engagement', 'Both passages emphasize the practice of meeting in the synagogue on the sabbath. This connection highlights the continuity of Jewish worship and teaching in early Christian ministry.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 14, 44, 9, 20, 20, 'synagogue', 'Preaching in Synagogues', 'This connection highlights the act of preaching in synagogues, as both passages mention this setting. Acts 13:14 describes entering a synagogue, while Acts 9:20 emphasizes preaching within them.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 14, 44, 13, 42, 42, 'sabbath day', 'Sabbath Day Preaching Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of the sabbath day for preaching. The first passage mentions going into the synagogue on the sabbath, while the second highlights the Gentiles'' desire for preaching on the next sabbath.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 15, 58, 13, 22, 22, 'word of exhortation', 'Exhortation in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of exhortation. In Acts, the rulers invite exhortation, while Hebrews urges the audience to ''suffer the word of exhortation.'' This connection highlights the importance of encouragement in the early Christian community.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 15, 44, 15, 21, 21, 'reading of the law and the prophets', 'Reading of the Law and Prophets', 'Both passages emphasize the reading of the law in synagogues. Acts 13:15 mentions the reading of the law and prophets, while Acts 15:21 states that Moses is preached in every city, being read in synagogues every Sabbath.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 15, 41, 5, 22, 22, 'rulers of the synagogue', 'Rulers of the Synagogue Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of rulers of the synagogue. In Acts, rulers invite exhortation, while in Mark, Jairus, a ruler, seeks Jesus'' help.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 15, 42, 4, 16, 18, 'reading of the law and the prophets', 'Reading in the Synagogue', 'Both passages emphasize the act of reading scripture in the synagogue, highlighting its significance in Jewish worship. In Acts, the rulers invite exhortation after the reading, while in Luke, Jesus reads from the prophet Isaiah, demonstrating the continuity of this practice.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 15, 44, 13, 27, 27, NULL, 'Connection of Prophetic Knowledge', 'This connection highlights the theme of knowledge of the prophets. Both passages emphasize the importance of recognizing the voices of the prophets read in the synagogue.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 15, 45, 12, 8, 8, 'any word of exhortation for the people', 'Exhortation and Leadership Connection', 'This connection highlights the role of exhortation in both passages. Acts 13:15 invites exhortation, while Romans 12:8 emphasizes the importance of exhortation as a spiritual gift.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 15, 46, 14, 3, 3, 'any word of exhortation for the people', 'Exhortation in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the theme of exhortation present in both passages. Acts 13:15 invites exhortation for the people, while 1 Corinthians 14:3 describes the purpose of prophecy as edification and exhortation.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 16, 44, 12, 17, 17, 'beckoning with his hand', 'Connection through Beckoning Gesture', 'Both passages emphasize the act of beckoning with the hand, indicating a call for attention or silence. This gesture serves as a pivotal moment in each context, highlighting the importance of communication in their respective narratives.', 'parallel', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 16, 44, 10, 2, 2, 'ye that fear God', 'Connection of God-fearing Individuals', 'Both passages emphasize individuals who ''feared God.'' This connection highlights the importance of reverence towards God in the early church.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 16, 5, 32, 46, 47, 'give audience', 'Call to Attention and Obedience', 'This connection highlights the call for attention in both passages. Paul urges the listeners to ''give audience,'' paralleling the command in Deuteronomy to ''set your hearts'' to the words of the law.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 16, 11, 8, 40, 40, 'ye that fear God', 'Connection of Fear and Audience', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''fear'' in relation to God. In Acts, Paul calls upon those who fear God to listen, while in 1 Kings, the fear of God is presented as a desired outcome for the people in the land.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 16, 19, 49, 1, 3, 'give audience', 'Call to Listen', 'This connection highlights the call to listen found in both passages. Paul invites the audience to ''give audience,'' while the psalmist urges all people to ''give ear.''', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 16, 19, 67, 7, 7, 'ye that fear God', 'Connection of Blessing and Fear', 'This connection highlights the theme of reverence towards God. Both passages emphasize the idea that those who receive God''s blessings will respond with fear or reverence, linking the Jewish audience in Acts to the broader call in Psalms.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 16, 33, 3, 8, 9, 'give audience', 'Call to Hear and Judgment', 'This connection highlights the call to listen in both passages. Paul urges the audience to ''give audience,'' while Micah implores the ''heads of the house of Jacob'' to ''hear this.'' Both emphasize the importance of heeding God''s message regarding judgment.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 17, 5, 7, 6, 8, NULL, 'Divine Choice and Redemption', 'Both passages emphasize God''s choice of Israel and His act of redemption from Egypt. They highlight that God chose Israel not for their numbers but because of His love and promises to their ancestors.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 17, 19, 105, 23, 24, 'the people when they dwelt as strangers', 'Israel''s Sojourn in Egypt', 'Both passages emphasize Israel''s time in Egypt and God''s role in their increase and deliverance. Acts 13:17 highlights God''s action in bringing them out, while Psalms 105:23-24 notes their growth during their stay.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 17, 23, 63, 9, 14, 'brought he them out of it', 'Divine Redemption and Guidance', 'Both passages emphasize God''s active role in redeeming Israel from Egypt and leading them through the wilderness. They highlight God''s compassion and the significance of His presence in guiding His people.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 17, 44, 7, 2, 53, 'with an high arm brought he them out of it', 'God''s Deliverance of Israel', 'Both passages emphasize God''s role in delivering Israel from bondage. Acts 13:17 mentions God''s high arm in bringing the people out of Egypt, while Acts 7:36 recounts how Moses was sent to deliver them after showing wonders in Egypt.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 17, 1, 12, 1, 3, 'the God of this people of Israel', 'Divine Selection and Blessing', 'This connection highlights God''s choice of Israel and His promise to Abram. Both passages emphasize God''s intention to create a great nation and bless His people.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 17, 1, 17, 7, 8, 'the people when they dwelt as strangers', 'Covenant and Exile Connection', 'This connection highlights God''s promise to Israel regarding their land and His role as their God. Both passages emphasize the theme of God''s chosen people dwelling as strangers before receiving the land of Canaan.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 17, 2, 1, 7, 9, 'exalted the people', 'God''s Deliverance of Israel', 'Both passages emphasize God''s role in the exaltation and multiplication of the Israelites. Acts 13:17 references their deliverance from Egypt, while Exodus 1:7-9 describes their growth and strength in the land before their exodus.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 18, 44, 7, 36, 36, 'forty years', 'Connection of Wilderness Experience', 'Both passages emphasize the forty years spent in the wilderness, highlighting a significant period of suffering and divine guidance for the Israelites. This connection illustrates the continuity of God''s actions during their journey from Egypt to the Promised Land.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 18, 2, 16, 2, 2, 'forty years suffered he their manners', 'Israel''s Wilderness Experience', 'This connection highlights the suffering of the Israelites during their forty years in the wilderness, as noted in Acts 13:18, and their complaints against Moses and Aaron in Exodus 16:2. Both passages emphasize the challenges faced by the Israelites during this period.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 18, 2, 16, 35, 35, 'forty years', 'Connection of Forty Years in Wilderness', 'This connection highlights the shared theme of the Israelites'' forty years in the wilderness, where they experienced God''s provision. Both passages emphasize the duration of this period and the sustenance provided until they reached the Promised Land.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
